-@title = "jQuery Mobile Docs - Select options"
= render :partial => "/mobile/index.js.haml", :format => :js

.type-interior{"data-role" => "page"}
  %div{"data-role" => "header", "data-theme" => "f"}
    %h1 Select Menus
    %a.ui-btn-right.jqm-home{"data-direction" => "reverse", "data-icon" => "home", "data-iconpos" => "notext", :href => "/mobile"} Home
  / /header
  %div{"data-role" => "content"}
    .content-primary
      %form{:action => "#", :method => "get"}
        %h2 Select menus
        %ul.localnav{"data-role" => "controlgroup", "data-type" => "horizontal"}
          %li
            %a{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/selects"} Basics
          %li
            %a.ui-btn-active{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/selects/options"} Options
          %li
            %a{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/selects/methods"} Methods
          %li
            %a{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/selects/events"} Events
        %p The select menu plugin has the following options:
        %dl
          %dt
            %code corners
            %em boolean
          %dd
            %p.default default: true
            %p
              Applies the theme button border-radius to the select button if set to true. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-corners=&quot;false&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { corners: "false" }
                );
          %dt
            %code icon
            %em string
          %dd
            %p.default default: "arrow-down"
            %p
              Applies an icon from the
              %a{:href => "/mobile/docs/buttons/buttons_icons"} icon set
              to the custom button. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-icon=&quot;star&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { icon: "star" }
                );
          %dt
            %code iconpos
            %em string
          %dd
            %p.default default: "right"
            %p
              Position of the icon in the select button. Possible values: left, right, none, notext. The notext value will display the select as an icon-only button with no text feedback. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-iconpos=&quot;left&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { iconpos: "left" }
                );
          %dt
            %code iconshadow
            %em boolean
          %dd
            %p.default default: true
            %p
              Applies the theme shadow to the select button if set to true. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-iconshadow=&quot;false&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { iconshadow: "false" }
                );
          %dt
            %code initSelector
            %em CSS selector string
          %dd
            %p.default default: "select:not(:jqmData(role='slider'))"
            %p
              This is used to define the selectors (element types, data roles, etc.) that will automatically be initialized as select menus. To change which elements are initialized, bind this option to the
              = succeed ":" do
                %a{:href => "/mobile/docs/api/globalconfig"} mobileinit event
            %pre
              %code
                :preserve
                  $( document ).bind( "mobileinit", function(){
                    $.mobile.selectmenu.prototype.options.initSelector = ".myselect";
                  });
          %dt
            %code inline
            %em boolean
          %dd
            %p.default default: null (false)
            %p
              If set to true, this will make the select button act like an inline button so the width is determined by the button's text. By default, this is null (false) so the select button is full width, regardless of the feedback content. Possible values: true, false. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-inline=&quot;true&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { inline: "true" }
                );
          %dt
            %code nativeMenu
            %em boolean
          %dd
            %p.default default: true
            %p
              When set to true, clicking the custom-styled select menu will open the native select menu which is best for performance. If set to false, the custom select menu style will be used instead of the native menu. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-native-menu=&quot;false&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { nativeMenu: "false" }
                );
          %dt
            %code shadow
            %em boolean
          %dd
            %p.default default: true
            %p
              Applies the drop shadow style to the select button if set to true. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-shadow=&quot;false&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { shadow: "false" }
                );
          %dt
            %code theme
            %em string
          %dd
            %p.default default: null, inherited from parent
            %p
              Sets the color scheme (swatch) for all instances of this widget. It accepts a single letter from a-z that maps to the swatches included in your theme. By default, it will inherit the same swatch color as it's parent container if not explicitly set. This option is also exposed as a data attribute:
              %code data-theme=&quot;a&quot;
            %pre
              %code
                $('select').selectmenu(
                %strong> { theme: "a" }
                );
    / /content-primary
